#originalStanceText=No
#originalTopic=Debate:_DC_handgun_ban
Cities that have gun ban laws enacted are not significantly safer The examples of Washington DC and New York show that with a gun ban law they are one of the most dangerous cities within the US. This leads to the conclusion that reality should have reinforced the reasoning that gunning bans  provides more safety to the public. Absent of this confirmation one can argue that banning guns is not an effective way of ensuring public safety."
